window.bookSummaryJSON = "In this unparalleled work of investigative journalism, Ronald Kessler reveals the inner world of the C.I.A. Based on extensive research and hundreds of interviews, including two with active directors of Central Intelligence, William H. Webster and Robert M. Gates, and with three former D.C.I.s, <i>Inside the C.I.A.</i> is the first in-depth, unbiased account of the Agency's core operations, its abject failures, and its resounding successes."; 
